Remove sentence about Upper/Lower Cappadocia. It is ungrammatical, lacks citations, invents terms that aren't used elsewhere and refers to content/pages that don't exist

Greek population was not expelled from Turkey. There was a population exchange agreement signed between Turkey and Greece in Lausanne, as a result of a request from the most prominent political figure of that time period, Eleftherios Venizelos. Greece needed numbers to enrich Greece, that is why Venizelos proposed this exchange to the League of Nations.
